<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-225-339 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 347 444</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 5 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Suit against Compuserve moves ahead. (class action suit by formerusers of The Source)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   CompuServe Inc. (Cases).andO;Product:   The Source (Data base) (Cases).andO;Topic:     Data Base ProducersLaw SuitData Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>****SUIT AGAINST COMPUSERVE MOVES AHEAD 02/05/91 COLUMBUS, OHIO, U.S.A., 1991FEB 5 (NB) -- With all the complaints coming out about Prodigy policies, manypeople forget that other systems aren't universally loved.andP;  CompuServe won'tmake that mistake again, as it's been forced to defend itself against a classaction suit brought by former users of The Source, the online service itbought and closed in 1989.andM;The suit, filed in the Circuit Court of Cook County, alleges that Sourcemembers inherited by CompuServe in the deal were forced to accept an&quot;Executive Option&quot; membership to the system when their accounts weretransferred.andP;  The suit, filed by Chicago attorneys Paul Bernstein and BarryNeil Lowe, notes that the Executive Option costs $10/month while regularCompuServe membership carries a minimum charge of just $1.50 per month.andM;Bernstein explained his complaint in a note to Newsbytes this way.andO;&quot;CompuServe took all of the credit card information that we subscribers hadgiven to The Source and, without asking for any affirmative consent of anykind, involuntarily transferred all Source accounts to CompuServe, electingfor us, again, without affirmative consent, the more expensive ExecutiveService Option.&quot; CompuServe succeeded in getting the original complaintdismissed but a second, amended complaint has been allowed to go forward.andO;&quot;That means that the defendant, CompuServe, must now respond to our complaintand the case will proceed, says Bernstein, adding, &quot;The class of formerSource Subscribers numbers in excess of 50,000 individuals.andP;  We are pleasedto advise of this very positive ruling in defense of consumers in ourhigh-tech society and will keep all advised in the future.&quot;andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910205/Press Contact: Paul Bernstein, 312- 951-8451)</TEXT></DOC>